Aim: Write a Lex program to find the parameters given below. Consider as input a
question paper of an examination and find:
Date of examination, semester, number of questions, numbers of words, lines, small letters,
capital letters, digits, and special characters.


%{
#include <stdio.h>
%}
DATE ([0-9]{1,2}[" "]*"/"[" "]*){2}[0-9]{4}[" "]*
SEM ["I"|"V"]*|[" "]*
SPECIAL ":"|"."|","
DIGITS [0-9]
SMALL [a-z]
CAPITAL [A-Z]
%{
int wcount=0,spcount=0,dcount=0,lcount=0,scount=0,qcount=0,ccount=0;
%}
%%
[\t" "] {wcount++;}
{DATE} printf("Date of examination : %s\n",yytext);
{SPECIAL} {spcount++;}
{SEM} printf("Semester : %s\n",yytext);
{SMALL} {scount++;}
{CAPITAL} {ccount++;}
{DIGITS} {dcount++;}
\n {lcount++,wcount++;}
"?" {qcount++,spcount++;}
%%
void main(){
yyin=fopen("file.txt","r");
yylex();
printf("Number of Qs : %d\n",qcount);
printf("Word count : %d\n",wcount);
printf("Line count : %d\n",lcount);
printf("Small char count : %d\n",scount);
printf("Capital char count : %d\n",ccount);
printf("Digit count : %d\n",dcount++);
printf("Special character count : %d\n",spcount);
}
int yywrap()
{
return 1;
}


input:-
ABC College
Date: 8/9/2022 Sem: I, II, III, IV, V, VI, VII, VIII
Question1 : What are the benefits of tree plantation?
Question2 : What is water pollution?
Question3 : What should be done to avoid road accidents?
Question4 : What are your view on noise pollution?
Question5 : Why should people adopt pets?
Question6 : What is green gym?
Question7 : What norms must pe implemented to minimize the loss from construction to
environment?
Question8 : What is air pollution?


commands to run:-
flex program.l
gcc lex.yy.c